<p>I want to get instances who contain in their lists (firstsList or SecondsList) a specific user.<br> In my solution, the create criteria takes into account only the first list of users. It seems to be a bad usage of the logical OR </p>  <p><strong>Domain</strong><br></p>  <pre><code>class ClassA {     static hasMany =  [firstsList:User,SecondsList:User] } </code></pre>  <p><strong>Service</strong><br></p>  <pre><code>def idList =  ClassA.createCriteria().list () {  projections { distinct ( "id" )     property("name")     property("id") }  or {                     firstsList{eq("login", 'John')}                 SecondsList{eq("login", 'John')}                                   }  order("name","desc")  }  return idList </code></pre>